--This is an example new rule that you can enter.
--If you submit this rule it will have to be voted on by other players (as described by rule 1).
--A lot of other examples can be found in the left menu bar.
do
   --get your own player number
   me <- getProposerNumber_
   --create an output for me only
   let displayMsg _ = void $ newOutput_ (Just me) "Bravo!"
   --create a button for me, which will display the output when clicked
   void $ onInputButton_ "Click here:" displayMsg me

Display my friends

by kau
display the persons you friended
show more...
do
   let outputFriends pn = newOutput (Just pn) $ do
       (mfs :: Maybe [(PlayerNumber, PlayerNumber)])  <- readVar (V "Friends")
       case mfs of
          Just fs -> do
             let myFriendsPNs = nub $ [ f | (p,f) <- fs, p == pn ]
             myFriendsNames <- catMaybes <$> mapM getPlayerName myFriendsPNs
(...)

Code of the rule:

X
do
   let outputFriends pn = newOutput (Just pn) $ do
       (mfs :: Maybe [(PlayerNumber, PlayerNumber)])  <- readVar (V "Friends")
       case mfs of
          Just fs -> do
             let myFriendsPNs = nub $ [ f | (p,f) <- fs, p == pn ]
             myFriendsNames <- catMaybes <$> mapM getPlayerName myFriendsPNs
             return $ "My friends are: " ++ (intercalate "," myFriendsNames)
          Nothing -> return "No friends variable"
   pns <- liftEffect getAllPlayerNumbers
   mapM_ outputFriends pns

This rule was activated by rule 4.

Code of the rule:

X
do
   suppressRule_ 8
   let askFriend :: PlayerNumber -> Event (PlayerNumber)
       askFriend src = do
          pls <- liftEvent getAllPlayerNumbers
          options <- liftEvent $ mapM (\n -> getPlayerName n >>=  \pn -> return (n, fromMaybe "unnamed" pn)) pls
          guard (length pls >= 2) >> do
             dst <- inputRadio src "Make this player your friend: " (sort options)
             return dst
   let makeFriend :: PlayerNumber -> PlayerNumber -> Exp Effect ()
       makeFriend pn nf = do
          modifyVar (V "Friends") ((pn,nf):) 
          return ()
   void $ forEachPlayer_ (\pn -> void $ onEvent_ (askFriend pn) (makeFriend pn))

This rule was activated by rule 4.

18

Sponsored players

by kau
Let's try to bring more players! If you sponsor a new player, you get 3000 Blings.
show more...
-- new players will be asked whom sponsored them.
-- the designated person gets 3000 Blings.
do 
   let playerArriveSponsored :: Event PlayerNumber
       playerArriveSponsored = do
          pn <- _playerNumber <$> playerEvent Arrive
          isInvited <- inputRadio pn "Where you invited/sponsored by a player?" [(True, "Yes"), (False, "No")]
(...)

Code of the rule:

X
-- new players will be asked whom sponsored them.
-- the designated person gets 3000 Blings.
do 
   let playerArriveSponsored :: Event PlayerNumber
       playerArriveSponsored = do
          pn <- _playerNumber <$> playerEvent Arrive
          isInvited <- inputRadio pn "Where you invited/sponsored by a player?" [(True, "Yes"), (False, "No")]
          guard isInvited
          pls <- liftEvent getAllPlayerNumbers
          options <- liftEvent $ mapM (\n -> getPlayerName n >>=  \pn -> return (n, fromMaybe "unnamed" pn)) (pls \\ [pn])
          dst <- inputRadio pn "Which player invited you? " (sort options)
          return dst
   void $ onEvent_ playerArriveSponsored (\pn -> void $ modifyValueOfPlayer pn accounts (+3000))

This rule was activated by rule 4.

Tax!

    schedule_ (recur daily) $ do
        pnsWithAccounts <- liftEffect $ do
                              pns <- getAllPlayerNumbers

Code of the rule:

X
    schedule_ (recur daily) $ do
        pnsWithAccounts <- liftEffect $ do
                              pns <- getAllPlayerNumbers
                              pnsWithMaybeAccounts <- forM pns $ \pn -> do
                                                        amount <- getValueOfPlayer pn accounts
                                                        return $ (pn, amount)
                              return $ [(pn, x) | (pn, Just x) <- pnsWithMaybeAccounts]
        if null pnsWithAccounts then
            return ()
        else do
          let cmp (_, amount) (_, amount') = compare amount amount'
          let (richestPn, richestAmount) = maximumBy cmp pnsWithAccounts
          let n = length pnsWithAccounts
          let taxed = (75 * richestAmount) `div` 100
          let perPlayer = taxed `div` n
          let reallyTaxed = n * perPlayer
          modifyValueOfPlayer richestPn accounts (\x -> x - reallyTaxed)
          modifyAllValues accounts (\x -> x + perPlayer)

do
   let initialShopInventory = [(cockpit, 0 :: Int), (engine, 10), (fueltank, 100), (cargo, 100)]
       -- Obviously we shouldn't be attaching things to the burny side of an engine.
       engine = SpaceshipPart { partId = 2, partType = "engine", partPrice = 200, partConnectors = defConns { Spaceship.right = True, up = True, down = True } }

       -- Cargo is cheap, and can be put anywhere.

       defConns = PartConnectors { up = False, down = False, Spaceship.left = False, Spaceship.right = False }
       showPartInventory (SpaceshipPart { partType = name, partPrice = price }, count) = name ++ "\t(" ++ show count ++ " in stock):\t" ++ show price

   -- Create the shop with some inventory
   inventory <- newMsgVar_ "ShopInventory" initialShopInventory

   -- Players initially have empty inventories
   playerInventory <- newMsgVar_ "PlayerInventory" []
   void $ createValueForEachPlayer ([] :: [SpaceshipPart]) playerInventory

   -- Shop display
   void . outputAll $ do
      inv <- fromMaybe [] <$> readMsgVar inventory
      return . unlines $ "Shop inventory:" : map showPartInventory inv

        mmsgs <- readVar (V "comlog")
        flip (maybe (return "ERROR: cannot access comlog")) mmsgs $ \msgs -> do
            filtered <- showMyMessages $ filterMessages pid msgs
            if null filtered
              then return "No messages"
              else return . concat . intersperse "\n" $ filtered
    nothing

do
   let outputFriends pn = newOutput (Just pn) $ do
       (mfs :: Maybe [(PlayerNumber, PlayerNumber)])  <- readVar (V "Friends")

do
   suppressRule_ 8
   let askFriend :: PlayerNumber -> Event (PlayerNumber)
       askFriend src = do
          pls <- liftEvent getAllPlayerNumbers
          options <- liftEvent $ mapM (\n -> getPlayerName n >>=  \pn -> return (n, fromMaybe "unnamed" pn)) pls
          guard (length pls >= 2) >> do
             dst <- inputRadio src "Make this player your friend: " (sort options)
             return dst
   let makeFriend :: PlayerNumber -> PlayerNumber -> Exp Effect ()
       makeFriend pn nf = do
          modifyVar (V "Friends") ((pn,nf):) 
          return ()
   void $ forEachPlayer_ (\pn -> void $ onEvent_ (askFriend pn) (makeFriend pn))

-- new players will be asked whom sponsored them.
-- the designated person gets 3000 Blings.
do 
   let playerArriveSponsored :: Event PlayerNumber
       playerArriveSponsored = do
          pn <- _playerNumber <$> playerEvent Arrive
          isInvited <- inputRadio pn "Where you invited/sponsored by a player?" [(True, "Yes"), (False, "No")]
          guard isInvited
          pls <- liftEvent getAllPlayerNumbers
          options <- liftEvent $ mapM (\n -> getPlayerName n >>=  \pn -> return (n, fromMaybe "unnamed" pn)) (pls \\ [pn])
          dst <- inputRadio pn "Which player invited you? " (sort options)
          return dst
   void $ onEvent_ playerArriveSponsored (\pn -> void $ modifyValueOfPlayer pn accounts (+3000))

   let askUnFriend :: PlayerNumber -> Event (PlayerNumber)

Code of the rule:

X
do
    suppressRule_ 12 -- Fix for the non-working initial monies for new players
    
    let giveMoney :: PlayerNumber -> Maybe Int -> Int -> Nomex ()
        giveMoney _ Nothing _ = return ()
        giveMoney pn (Just money) n = void $ modifyValueOfPlayer pn accounts $ (+ amount)
            where amount = abs $ money `quot` n
        
    let shareMoneyBetweenPlayers :: PlayerNumber -> Nomex ()
        shareMoneyBetweenPlayers pn = do
            nbPlayers <- liftEffect $ getPlayersNumber
            money <- liftEffect $ getValueOfPlayer pn accounts
            forEachPlayer_ $ \pn -> giveMoney pn money nbPlayers
            return () -- weird but won't return () elsewise
    
    void $ onEvent_ (playerEvent Leave) (\pi -> shareMoneyBetweenPlayers (_playerNumber pi))

29

Tax!

by dentuk
All players share 75% of the richest player's money (daily event)
show more...
    schedule_ (recur daily) $ do
        pnsWithAccounts <- liftEffect $ do
                              pns <- getAllPlayerNumbers
                              pnsWithMaybeAccounts <- forM pns $ \pn -> do
                                                        amount <- getValueOfPlayer pn accounts
                                                        return $ (pn, amount)
                              return $ [(pn, x) | (pn, Just x) <- pnsWithMaybeAccounts]
(...)

Code of the rule:

X
    schedule_ (recur daily) $ do
        pnsWithAccounts <- liftEffect $ do
                              pns <- getAllPlayerNumbers
                              pnsWithMaybeAccounts <- forM pns $ \pn -> do
                                                        amount <- getValueOfPlayer pn accounts
                                                        return $ (pn, amount)
                              return $ [(pn, x) | (pn, Just x) <- pnsWithMaybeAccounts]
        if null pnsWithAccounts then
            return ()
        else do
          let cmp (_, amount) (_, amount') = compare amount amount'
          let (richestPn, richestAmount) = maximumBy cmp pnsWithAccounts
          let n = length pnsWithAccounts
          let taxed = (75 * richestAmount) `div` 100
          let perPlayer = taxed `div` n
          let reallyTaxed = n * perPlayer
          modifyValueOfPlayer richestPn accounts (\x -> x - reallyTaxed)
          modifyAllValues accounts (\x -> x + perPlayer)

This rule was activated by rule 4.

do
    let askChat :: PlayerNumber -> Event (UTCTime, PlayerNumber, String)
        askChat from = do
            others <- sort . filter (/= from) <$> liftEvent getAllPlayerNumbers
            guard (length others >= 1) >> do
                to <- inputRadio' from "to: " others
                msg <- inputText from "message: "
                time <- liftEvent getCurrentTime
                return (time, to, msg)
        sendChat :: PlayerNumber -> (UTCTime, PlayerNumber, String) -> Nomex ()
        sendChat from (time, to, msg) = void $ modifyVar (V "comlog") ((time, from, to, msg) :)

    void $ forEachPlayer_ (\from -> void $ onEvent_ (askChat from) (sendChat from))

Parts Shop/Inventory

by prototrout
A shop with an inventory of parts. This rule also creates players' individual inventories.
show more...
do
   let initialShopInventory = [(cockpit, 0 :: Int), (engine, 10), (fueltank, 100), (cargo, 100)]
       -- Obviously we shouldn't be attaching things to the burny side of an engine.
       engine = SpaceshipPart { partId = 2, partType = "engine", partPrice = 200, partConnectors = defConns { Spaceship.right = True, up = True, down = True } }
       -- Fuel tanks can only attach above/below another part... Maybe they only fuel attached engines?
       fueltank = SpaceshipPart { partId = 3, partType = "fueltank", partPrice = 100, partConnectors = defConns { up = True, down = True } }
       -- Cargo is cheap, and can be put anywhere.
(...)

Code of the rule:

X
do
   let initialShopInventory = [(cockpit, 0 :: Int), (engine, 10), (fueltank, 100), (cargo, 100)]
       -- Obviously we shouldn't be attaching things to the burny side of an engine.
       engine = SpaceshipPart { partId = 2, partType = "engine", partPrice = 200, partConnectors = defConns { Spaceship.right = True, up = True, down = True } }
       -- Fuel tanks can only attach above/below another part... Maybe they only fuel attached engines?
       fueltank = SpaceshipPart { partId = 3, partType = "fueltank", partPrice = 100, partConnectors = defConns { up = True, down = True } }
       -- Cargo is cheap, and can be put anywhere.
       cargo = SpaceshipPart { partId = 4, partType = "cargo", partPrice = 50, partConnectors = defConns { Spaceship.left = True, Spaceship.right = True, up = True, down = True } }
       defConns = PartConnectors { up = False, down = False, Spaceship.left = False, Spaceship.right = False }
       showPartInventory (SpaceshipPart { partType = name, partPrice = price }, count) = name ++ "\t(" ++ show count ++ " in stock):\t" ++ show price

   -- Create the shop with some inventory
   inventory <- newMsgVar_ "ShopInventory" initialShopInventory

   -- Players initially have empty inventories
   playerInventory <- newMsgVar_ "PlayerInventory" []
   void $ createValueForEachPlayer ([] :: [SpaceshipPart]) playerInventory

   -- Shop display
   void . outputAll $ do
      inv <- fromMaybe [] <$> readMsgVar inventory
      return . unlines $ "Shop inventory:" : map showPartInventory inv

This rule was activated by rule 40.

      return $ fromMaybe "??" $ do
         d <- md
         lookup partName d 
   showShip :: Spaceship -> NomexNE String
   showShip (Spaceship parts _) = do
      ps <- mapM showPart parts 
      return $ intercalate "  " ps
   displayShip :: PlayerNumber -> Nomex ()
   displayShip pn = void $ newOutput (Just pn) $ do
      mss <- readVar (V "spaceships" :: V [(PlayerNumber, Spaceship)])
      case (mss >>= lookup pn) of
         Just s -> showShip s
         Nothing -> return "Cannot display spaceship"

do
   suppressRule_ 2
   setVictory $ do
     (fs :: [(PlayerNumber, PlayerNumber)])  <- fromMaybe [] <$> readVar (V "Friends")
     pls <- getAllPlayerNumbers
     let winners = [ p |
            p <- pls,
            let mutual = [o | (o, p') <- fs, p == p' ],
            let friends = [o | (p', o) <- fs, p == p' ],
            let mutual_friends = [o | o <- friends, o `elem` mutual ],
            length mutual_friends >= 5 ]
     return winners

do
   suppressRule_ 2
   setVictory $ do
     (fs :: [(PlayerNumber, PlayerNumber)])  <- fromMaybe [] <$> readVar (V "Friends")
     pls <- getAllPlayerNumbers
     let winners = [ p |
            p <- pls,
            let quorum = length pls - 1,
            let mutual = [o | (o, p') <- fs, p == p' ],
            let friends = [o | (p', o) <- fs, p == p' ],
            let mutual_friends = [o | o <- friends, o `elem` mutual ],
            length mutual_friends >= quorum]
     return winners
